Your Honor,

I, Aleksander Nowak, stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of assault. I acknowledge my role in pushing my employee to the ground and subsequently delivering a kick to his stomach.

Allow me to provide some background on the circumstances that led to this regrettable incident. My motivation stemmed from a deeply rooted frustration arising from the significant mistake my employee had made at work. The gravity of this error threatened to inflict substantial financial damage upon my company. Overwhelmed by anger and disappointment, I momentarily lost control of my emotions, resulting in the assault.

I want to express my deep regret for my impulsive actions and the harm I have caused. I understand the seriousness of my offense and take full responsibility for my behavior. I have no prior criminal record, and this incident is an isolated occurrence that does not reflect my character or values as a member of society.

Your Honor, I come before you today fully aware of the gravity of my actions and the consequences they have inflicted upon the victim. I plead guilty to the charge of assault, fully acknowledging the severity of this offense. I am prepared to accept any and all appropriate penalties deemed fit by the court.

I humbly request your mercy and consideration in determining my sentence. This incident has served as a profound awakening for me, compelling me to reflect upon and address the factors that led to this act of aggression. I am committed to utilizing this experience as a catalyst for personal growth and self-improvement, ensuring that such actions never repeat themselves.

Once again, I express my sincere remorse for the pain and distress I have caused. I thank the court for the opportunity to present my plea and respectfully await your decision.

Thank you.
